				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ESR={W}_{S}/{W}_{D}$$\end{document}, here ESR represents the equilibrium swelling rate. WS represents the mass of the hydrogel after swelling equilibrium, and WD represents the mass of the dry hydrogel.
